This paper is primarily focused on deep learning models for natural language processing, specifically neural machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the Transformer model, which is a state-of-the-art model for machine translation, and this is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of Tensor2Tensor, which is a library for deep learning models, and this falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks for image processing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for sequence-to-sequence problems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
